Description:
This Java Swing-based ToDo List application provides users with a simple and intuitive
interface to manage their daily tasks. The application includes a login feature for secure 
access and a main dashboard where users can add tasks, mark them as completed, set task deadlines,
and clear finished tasks. The UI is designed with a pleasant color scheme for a visually appealing
experience.


Key Features:

Login System: Secure user authentication with a username and password.
Task Management: Add, mark as done, and set deadlines for tasks.
Dynamic Lists: Tasks are displayed in a dynamic list with automatic indexing.
Clear Finished Tasks: Easily remove completed tasks to keep the list organized.
TitleBar: Welcoming title bar at the top of the main window.


How to Use:

Run the application and log in with the provided credentials.
Use the "Add Task" button to create new tasks.
Mark tasks as done by clicking the "Done" button.
Set deadlines for tasks using the "Set Time" button.
Clear finished tasks with the "Clear finished tasks" button.


Dependencies:

Java Swing Library
